{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a33fef14-cece-449b-b1e3-613316b33464","content":"Here's how to migrate your xUnit.net test project to Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n\n**1. Update package references** in your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<!-- Remove -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.visualstudio\" Version=\"...\" />\n\n<!-- Add -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.mtp\" Version=\"1.0.0\" />\n```\n\n**2. Enable MTP** in your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n**3. Run tests** with:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test\n```\n\nOr run the test project directly as an executable (MTP makes test projects self-contained apps):\n\n```bash\ndotnet run --project YourTests.csproj -- --help\n```\n\n**Key notes:**\n- `xunit.runner.mtp` replaces `xunit.runner.visualstudio` — keep `xunit` (2.9.3+) as-is.\n- The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property ensures `dotnet test` uses MTP instead of VSTest.\n- No test code changes are needed — your `[Fact]` and `[Theory]` tests work unchanged.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d8031783-7eef-446f-996e-ab50a1c9f528","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using `xunit.runner.visualstudio`) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP). Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of this migration path.","outputTokens":384},"id":"ce5cb8d1-de8c-4f22-9a6c-d3255f6c0c23","timestamp":"2026-04-07T15:54:17.948Z","parentId":"4d7743f7-3642-435d-9220-5e8479c9ae24"}
